SIMPLE: polygenetic
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Polygenetic
<hw>Pol`y*ge*net"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having many distinct sources; originating at various places or
times.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to polygenesis;
polyphyletic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Polygenetic mountain range</b></col> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>,
<cd>one which is composite, or consists of two or more monogenetic
ranges, each having had its own history of development.</cd>
<rj><au>Dana.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polygenic</ent>⟦br⟧
